

## TASK-002 Complete: Finite Metric Spaces

### Files Changed
1. **`src/knn_stability/metrics.py`** - Full implementation of `FiniteMetricSpace` class and `is_valid_metric` helper
2. **`tests/test_metrics.py`** - Comprehensive test suite with 20 new tests

### Implementation Summary

**`FiniteMetricSpace` class:**
- Represents a finite metric space (X, d) as indexed points + validated distance matrix
- Validates all metric axioms on construction:
  - ✅ Square matrix check
  - ✅ Symmetry check (`d[i,j] = d[j,i]`)
  - ✅ Non-negative distances
  - ✅ Zero diagonal (`d[i,i] = 0`)
  - ✅ Triangle inequality (`d[i,k] ≤ d[i,j] + d[j,k]`)
- Public API: `n` property, `d(i, j)` method, `__repr__`, `__eq__`

**`is_valid_metric` helper:**
- Returns `True`/`False` without raising exceptions

### Tests Added
- 20 focused tests covering:
  - Basic construction (empty, single point, two points)
  - Validation rejection cases (non-square, asymmetric, negative, non-zero diagonal, triangle violation)
  - Edge cases (integer input, float32 conversion, dimension checks)
  - Helper function behavior
  - String representation and equality

### Test Results
```
26 passed in 0.08s
